devices.desc: The type of device(s) the users of your target organization use for their daily work may be important if you are selling a product or service that is better used on certain types of devices. For e.g. android only apps can be promoted to android smartphone users. If so, select this option.
devices.name: Device Preference

hasNeed.desc: This is to be opted (by your team) only when the target user / organization has expressly advised that they need a similar solution as yours.
hasNeed.name: Has Need

hasTime.desc: This is to be opted (by your team) only when the target user / organization gives actual time range. For e.g., within a month, by 25th, etc.
hasTime.name: Has Time

prevExp.desc: It may (or not) be easy to promote your solution to someone already familiar with a similar solution. If so, select this option.
prevExp.name: Prior experience in using a similar product

teamSize.desc: If our product / service may be catering to a specific department with an organization and is advantageous to specific team sizes, select this option. (Enter ONLY the MAX team size in the TYPE Field. E.g., 10. Which translates internally as up to 10 team members).
teamSize.name: Team Size

turnover.desc: When a company's annual turnover is a good indicator for your type of product / service choose this option. (Enter ONLY the MAX annual turnover in the TYPE Field. E.g., 10000. Which translates internally as UP TO 1000 USD or Euros as per the currency you set up during onboarding.).
turnover.name: Annual Turnover Ranges

cityTypes.desc: Some solutions are apt for Tier 2 cities while other solutions sell mostly in Tier 1 cities. And so on... Choose this option if you want to prioritize by the city where your target organization is located.
cityTypes.name: Type of City

hasBudget.desc: This is to be opted (by your team) only when the target user / organization gives actual budget indications.
hasBudget.name: Has Budget

locations.desc: You may be prioritizing success rates depending upon broad location types (By countries or continents). If so, enable this option. For e.g., The Americas, Europe, etc.
locations.name: Locations

industries.desc: Some companies sell to specific industries. If so, select this option.
industries.name: Industry Types

yearStarted.desc: We've seen this sometimes, where a certain company would like to promote their solutions only to companies established after 2010 (E.g.). If such considerations are important for you choose this option.
yearStarted.name: Established Year (Range)

buyingStages.desc: As a sales person it is important to know where the target organization stands in their search for a solution.
buyingStages.name: Buying Stage

companyTypes.desc: Answers the question - What are the ideal Organization Types for our business?
companyTypes.name: Company Types

businessTypes.desc: Sometimes it is possible to have both B2C and B2B as users of your solution. It is quite rare. If this applies to you choose this option.
businessTypes.name: B2C / B2B

companyStages.desc: Some solutions are sold according to what stage the target company is in at that moment. For e.g., it may (or not) be prudent to sell highly analytical solutions to companies in Growth+ stages.
companyStages.name: Stage of Company

empCountRange.desc: When a target company's employee count matters for your product, choose this option. (Enter ONLY the MAX employee count in the TYPE Field. E.g., 1000. Which translates internally as up to 1000 employees).
empCountRange.name: Employee Count / Range

keyPainPoints.desc: A summary of problems uncovered that will help tailor make your pitch and sales processes.
keyPainPoints.name: Key Pain Points

longTermGoals.desc: In general, understanding long term and short term goals of the organization can help your sales person perform better. If so, choose this option.
longTermGoals.name: Long Term Goals

techSavviness.desc: The target organization being tech savvy (or not) may be an important consideration for using your products and services. If so, select this option.
techSavviness.name: Tech Savviness

workingStyles.desc: This option is used to capture information about how your target company works. For e.g., they do all work online, or they only do field work, etc.
workingStyles.name: Company Work Style

shortTermGoals.desc: In general, understanding long term and short term goals of the organization can help your sales person perform better. If so, choose this option.
shortTermGoals.name: Short Term Goals

currentSolutions.desc: Understanding how they are currently (trying to) solving their problems is a good information to have while selling.
currentSolutions.name: Current solution type
